snippet.textDisplay: Sorry Stephen, but as a life long Cowboys fan, the last thing you would want is Jerry to make a "flashy" hire.  I also find it odd that it seems to Stephen that Mike McCarthy is the only human incapable of learning from their past mistakes.  How many coaches had John Elway and could not win a Super Bowl, so even great QB's/players need the right coach.  It is kind of like in Basketball how people dump on Phil Jackson for not being a great coach because he had so many super stars.  Yet the Lakers with all their star power could not win under other coaches, then Phil came, and they won championships.  Heck when he was fired from Cleveland, Billichick was considered a failed coach.

snippet.textDisplay: It's just not a great move to say to the fans that we are building a dynasty because they're more in the mode of making a one hit wonder. Now I understand that most teams only win one Super Bowl but this isn't just any organization this is the Dallas Cowboys a franchise that expects to break records.  They stand for something more than any team in the league if you really meant business you would have hired Urban Meyer and been patient because there's a lot of players on this team right now that do not belong there because they are not there to win, their not disciplined and they don't care to be. I would have done what worked in the past higher Urban Meyer just like you hired Jimmy Johnson to lead the organization into the future with that you have a great chance of dominating years but instead we have a let's win now mentality and maybe we get a Super Bowl out of it that's not what us fans want, NO we want something that's long term.
